cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.CE

The paper involves natural language processing (NLP) and supervised machine learning methods for automatically detecting tweets by users reporting their birth defect outcomes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also deals with large-scale epidemiological research, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper involves data analysis and classification, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
